            <biogHist>
                <p>John Stewart was born on North Uist around 1786, the son of tenant farmer Angus
                    and Rachel (née McLeod) Stewart.  He married Marion ( née Cameron) and they had
                    at least three children - Mary, Archibald and Rachel; the family appear to have
                    been based in Baleshare, North Uist from 1851.  He died on 12th December 1867 in
                    Baleshare of unknown causes. On 23rd March 1869, Alexander Carmichael collected
                    a song from Flora MacLeod called  'Na H-Iolairean' beginning 'A Dhun dui sin ’s
                    a Dhun dui' whch she told him she had heard from John Stewart (GB 237
                    Coll-97/CW107/28); on the same day, Carmichael made some notes about John
                    Stewart who had died two years previously.  Stewart had heard that Carmichael
                    was searching for 'old things' and wanted to 'unburd[en] his mind' to Carmichael
                    but never did although as Carmichael states 'I so often wished''.</p>
